This paper deals with the application of differential privacy in machine learning, specifically in stochastic gradient descent. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the potential disparate impact of differential privacy on certain groups, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper proposes a modified algorithm to mitigate this impact, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the experimental evaluation of the proposed algorithm, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
